sourceQuestion:
Which of the following languages are undecidable? Note that <M> indicates encoding of the Turing machine M.

L_1 = {<M> | L(M) = empty}
L_2 = {<M, w, q> | M on input w reaches state q in exactly 100 steps}
L_3 = {<M> | L(M) is not recursive}
L_4 = {<M> | L(M) contains at least 21 numbers}

A. L_1, L_2, and L_3 only
B. L_2 and L_4 only
C. L_1, L_3, and L_4 only
D. L_1, L_2, and L_4 only

